HEADWORD: Parapegm
<hw>Par"a*pegm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>parapegma</ets>, Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to fix beside; <grk>para`</grk>
beside + <?/ to fix: cf. F. <ets>parapegme</ets>.]</ety> <def>An
engraved tablet, usually of brass, set up in a public place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Parapegms</xex> were used for the publication of
laws, proclamations, etc., and the recording of astronomical phenomena
or calendar events.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parapeptone</ent>⟦br⟧
